org.aoplib4j.uml
Class DFSDiagramWriter

java.lang.Object
  org.aoplib4j.uml.SequenceDiagramWriter
      org.aoplib4j.uml.DFSDiagramWriter
Direct Known Subclasses:
CodeToDiagramWriter, PngWriter, SEQUENCEWriter
public abstract class DFSDiagramWriter
extends SequenceDiagramWriter

Class implementing the Depth-first search (DFS) (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Depth-first_search) on the sequence method. (since a SequenceMethod is a tree structure). This class represents the AbstractClass from the Template Method Pattern (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template_method_pattern). Every subclass must implement the way of writing the diagrams.

Author:
Adrian Citu

writeMethod

private void writeMethod(SequenceMethod meth)
                  throws java.io.IOException
Write the content for a method. The workflow is :
  • call writeMethodBeforeChildren(SequenceMethod)
  • for every child method method call writeMethod(SequenceMethod)
  • call writeMethodAfterChildren(SequenceMethod)

Parameters:
meth - the method to write.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if any exception when writing.
